Name: C library providing BLAKE2b, BLAKE2s, BLAKE2bp, BLAKE2sp
Files: src/blake2b.c src/blake2b-load-sse2.h src/blake2b-load-sse41.h src/blake2bp.c src/blake2bp-test.c src/blake2b-ref.c src/blake2b-round.h src/blake2b-test.c src/blake2-config.h src/blake2-dispatch.c src/blake2.h src/blake2-impl.h src/blake2-kat.h src/blake2s.c src/blake2s-load-sse2.h src/blake2s-load-sse41.h src/blake2s-load-xop.h src/blake2sp.c src/blake2sp-test.c src/blake2s-ref.c src/blake2s-round.h src/blake2s-test.c
Description: BLAKE2 is a cryptographic hash function faster than MD5, SHA-1, SHA-2, and SHA-3, yet is at least as secure as the latest standard SHA-3.
